  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Overview&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    You will find that it is often necessary to edit a schedule in order to represent a workload properly. Although it is&#xD;
    possible to run a schedule with only one user group or one test to run, in the majority of cases you will want to edit&#xD;
    the schedule to reflect your workload requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    There are many ways to edit a schedule. You can, for example, add a user group, a test, loops, delays, or a random&#xD;
    selector. In this tool mentor, the focus will be on two of the more frequently encountered types of editing a schedule,&#xD;
    namely &lt;i>adding a user group&lt;/i> and &lt;i>adding a test&lt;/i>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Tool Steps&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Editing a Schedule by Adding a User Group&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Editing a Schedule by Adding a Test&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    1. Adding a User Group&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To edit a schedule by adding a user group, perform the following steps:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        In the Test Navigator, expand the project until you locate the schedule.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Right-click the schedule, and then click &lt;strong>Open&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        In the Schedule Editor, right-click the schedule, and then click &lt;strong>Add &amp;gt; User Group&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        In the &lt;strong>Group Name&lt;/strong> field, enter a descriptive name for the user group.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        In the &lt;strong>Group Size&lt;/strong> section, select Absolute or Percentage (where Absolute indicates a static number&#xD;
        of users and Percentage indicates a dynamic number of users), and then enter the number or percentage of users in&#xD;
        the group.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Decide whether the user group will run on your computer or on another computer.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To declare a remote location: &lt;!--    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;> -->&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;div style=&quot;MARGIN-LEFT: 2em&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;ol>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            Click &lt;strong>Add New&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            In the Add Location Wizard, select the project to store the location.&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            In the &lt;strong>File Name&lt;/strong> field, type the name of the file that will contain information about this&#xD;
            computer, and then click &lt;strong>Next&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            In the &lt;strong>Name&lt;/strong> field, enter a descriptive name for the remote computer.&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            In the &lt;strong>Hostname&lt;/strong> field, enter the IP address or the fully qualified host name of the remote&#xD;
            computer.&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            In the &lt;strong>Deployment Directory&lt;/strong> field, enter the directory on the remote computer that will store&#xD;
            the test assets. The directory, which is created if it does not exist, stores the temporary files that are&#xD;
            needed during a schedule run.&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            In the &lt;strong>Operating System&lt;/strong> field, select the operating system of the remote computer, and then&#xD;
            click &lt;strong>Finish&lt;/strong>&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;/div>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To add an already declared location: &lt;!--    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;> -->&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ol>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Click &lt;strong>Add Existing&lt;/strong>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                In the Select Location dialog box, select the computer on which the user group will run, and then click&#xD;
                &lt;strong>OK&lt;/strong>. &lt;!--            &lt;/li> -->&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ol>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    2. Adding a Test&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A test lets you emulate the action of an individual user.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To edit a schedule by adding a test, perform the following steps:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        In the Test Navigator, expand the project until you locate the schedule.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Right-click the schedule, and then click &lt;strong>Open&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Right-click the user group that will contain the test, and then click &lt;strong>Add &amp;gt; Test&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        In the Select Performance Tests dialog box, expand the project name to display the test that you want to add.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click the name of the test, and then click &lt;strong>OK&lt;/strong>. The test appears in the schedule.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; /> For more information on editing a schedule in&#xD;
IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Performance Tester, see the topic &lt;em>Representing workloads&lt;/em> in the Rational Performance Tester online&#xD;
Help.&lt;br /></mainDescription>
